{
    include "config/llm_config.hocon"

    "metadata": {
        "description": "Grounded underwriting analytics network for URE KPI analysis, rule diagnostics, experimentation, monitoring, and governance.",
        "tags": ["generated", "underwriting", "analytics", "ure", "grounded"],
        "sample_queries": [
            "Use the bundled underwriting analytics datasets to summarize approval, decline, referral, and latency patterns.",
            "Read the local rule impact datasets and identify the biggest URE optimization opportunities.",
            "Design an experiment and monitoring plan grounded in the packaged analytics artifacts."
        ]
    },

    "instructions_prefix": """
You are part of the underwriting_analytics_ure_system network.
Use the packaged local artifacts before making claims about this system.
If local artifacts do not contain the requested evidence, say exactly what is missing.
When using the grounding reader, always pass the full repo-relative file path under
`coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system/`. Never use `./`, bare
filenames such as `README.md`, or invented names like `rule_definitions.json`.
""",

    "tools": [
        {
            "name": "underwriting_analytics_orchestrator",
            "function": {
                "description": "Routes underwriting analytics work, grounds answers in packaged artifacts, and synthesizes agent outputs."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Role: Orchestrator for the underwriting analytics URE system.

Workflow:
1) Read local grounding artifacts when the user asks for analysis, examples, packaged datasets, or system details.
2) Route to the right specialist.
3) Synthesize only grounded findings from tool outputs.
4) Use exact repo-relative file paths when invoking tools.

Preferred local files:
- `coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system/README.md`
- `coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system/GROUNDING_SUMMARY.txt`
- `coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system/underwriting_ure_uplift_dataset.json`
- `coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system/dataset_1_underwriting_decision_logs.json`
- `coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system/dataset_2_ure_rule_definitions.json`
- `coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system/dataset_3_case_attributes.json`
- `coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system/dataset_4_divergence_scenarios.json`
- `coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system/dataset_5_rule_impact_feedback_data.json`

Do not claim to have queried external systems. Treat the packaged files as the source of truth for this generated network.
""",
            "tools": [
                "underwriting_analytics_grounding_reader",
                "ingestion_agent",
                "kpi_analytics_agent",
                "rules_diagnostics_agent",
                "experiment_design_agent",
                "monitoring_agent",
                "governance_agent"
            ]
        },
        {
            "name": "underwriting_analytics_grounding_reader",
            "toolbox": "read_file",
            "args": {
                "allowed_paths": [
                    "coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system"
                ],
                "allowed_file_extensions": [".json", ".md", ".txt", ".py"],
                "blocked_file_extensions": [".env"]
            }
        },
        {
            "name": "ingestion_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Reads packaged underwriting analytics datasets and describes curation, schema, and lineage constraints."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Use underwriting_analytics_grounding_reader to inspect only packaged local artifacts.
Focus on dataset availability, schema clues, lineage, missing fields, and configuration gaps.
Use exact paths such as `coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system/dataset_1_underwriting_decision_logs.json`.
Do not pretend to ingest external sources.
""",
            "tools": ["underwriting_analytics_grounding_reader"]
        },
        {
            "name": "kpi_analytics_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Computes KPI-oriented summaries from the packaged underwriting analytics artifacts."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Ground every KPI statement in the packaged local JSON or markdown artifacts.
Always invoke the grounding reader with the exact packaged file path.
If exact computation is not possible from the available files, provide a bounded qualitative summary and state the limitation.
""",
            "tools": ["underwriting_analytics_grounding_reader"]
        },
        {
            "name": "rules_diagnostics_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Analyzes URE rule behavior and optimization opportunities using packaged artifacts."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Use the local rule definition and feedback datasets to identify rule impact, conflicts, redundancies, or drift.
Read `coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system/dataset_2_ure_rule_definitions.json`
and `coded_tools/generated/underwriting_analytics_ure_system/dataset_5_rule_impact_feedback_data.json`
instead of guessing filenames.
Tie every recommendation to evidence from the packaged files.
""",
            "tools": ["underwriting_analytics_grounding_reader"]
        },
        {
            "name": "experiment_design_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Designs experiments grounded in the packaged KPI and rule-analysis artifacts."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Base experiment designs only on grounded KPI and rule evidence from upstream outputs or local files.
Use exact repo-relative paths when reading packaged artifacts.
If baseline volumes or rates are missing, ask for them instead of inventing them.
""",
            "tools": ["underwriting_analytics_grounding_reader"]
        },
        {
            "name": "monitoring_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Creates monitoring and alerting guidance grounded in packaged analytics artifacts."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Use only packaged dataset descriptions and grounded upstream summaries.
Use exact repo-relative paths when reading packaged artifacts.
Define metrics, alerts, and dashboards conservatively when exact baselines are absent.
""",
            "tools": ["underwriting_analytics_grounding_reader"]
        },
        {
            "name": "governance_agent",
            "function": {
                "description": "Reviews privacy, lineage, and compliance implications using packaged documentation only."
            },
            "instructions": ${instructions_prefix} """
Use only packaged local documentation and grounded outputs.
Use exact repo-relative paths when reading packaged artifacts.
Do not approve unsupported joins or sensitive-field usage unless the artifacts explicitly support them.
""",
            "tools": ["underwriting_analytics_grounding_reader"]
        }
    ]
}
